"{\"uid\": \"sports.yahoo.com-silver-bronze-favorite-olympic-colors-215420951.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"      Manage your account    ...  NANTERRE, France (AP) - The favorite colors for the red, white and blue at the Olympic swimming pool are silver and bronze.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.9945228163035476, \"rank\": 0.005507094466708325, \"text\": \"NANTERRE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 50, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8998921552444374, \"rank\": 0.11120780161601575, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 54, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9998447517867503, \"rank\": 0.00015527231762181709, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through four days at La Defense Arena, the mighty U.S. team has won a bunch of medals - 15 in all - but only two of them are gold.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seven silvers and six bronzes round out the tally.\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americansreached the medal podium in all three eventsTuesday night, but each time it was in the runner-up spot (with a bronze medal thrown into the mix, as well).\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regan Smith fell to her Australian rival Kaylee McKeown, who captured her second straight Olympic gold in the women's 100-meter backstroke.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1917458577321496e-23, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.5965453024871182, \"rank\": 0.5419075256871783, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was the world-record holder after a dazzling performance at the U.S. trials last month, but it was McKeown coming out on top in the race that really mattered.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew it was going to be such a fight,\\\" Smith said.\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Kaylee is an exceptional competitor,\\\"  The Americans also claimed the bronze with Katharine Berkoff, the daughter of four-time Olympic medalist David Berkoff.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.30352449570603e-16, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}, {\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Berkoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone wants to win,\\\" the third-place finisher said.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's the goal.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's such a tight field, so I knew it was going to be tough.\\\"\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was more of the same in the men's 800 freestyle, where defending Olympic champion Bobby Finke came up just short.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's Daniel Wiffen captured his country's first swimming gold medal since 1996.\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1287, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9938543452222999, \"rank\": 0.004011741127139999, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd be lying If I said I wasn't disappointed,\\\" Finke said.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was the first loser.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It always stings to not be able to defend your title.\\\"\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final event of the night, the Americans claimed yet another silver in the men's 4x200 freestyle relay, with Britain winning its second straight Olympic gold in that event.\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9849149657163021, \"rank\": 0.015316039763402222, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are always rooting for gold,\\\" said Drew Kibler, a member of the U.S. relay team.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1732, \"end\": 1743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drew Kibler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Kibler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That is the American standard.\\\"\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Standard_Companies\", \"score\": 0.9999998357238973, \"rank\": 1.4976955794181967e-07, \"text\": \"American standard\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Standard_Companies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Standard_Companies\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was certainly an improvement on the same race in Tokyo, when the Americans missed a medal with a shocking fourth-place showing.\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1864, \"end\": 1869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999995925585496, \"rank\": 4.046475103263298e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is a really special thing to be on that podium.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was really tough missing that podium a few years ago,\\\" Kibler said.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But we are always shooting for gold.\\\"\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Americans have nearly twice as many medals as any other nation, they trail rival Australia in the race for shiniest color.\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9795761282269143, \"rank\": 0.020828825321022704, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The swimmers from Down Under have four victories and eight medals overall.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The thing that is most important is that we are pushing the sport in the right direction,\\\" Smith said.\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our rivalry is great for attention in the sport.\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have so much respect for each other.\\\"\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy has matched the Americans with two wins, and seven other nations have claimed golds in a sign of the sport's growing depth around the globe.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999795107392365, \"rank\": 2.0485446234865402e-05, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. has plenty of chances to add to its medal haul over the final five days of swimming.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans would prefer a few more trips to the top step on the podium.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2756, \"end\": 2769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.30352449570603e-16, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"___  AP Summer Olympics:https://apnews.com/hub/2024-paris-olympic-games\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": []}]}"